# Quality Checklist — Run After Every Build

## Code quality
- [ ] All CSS classes used in HTML are defined in the stylesheet
- [ ] All JS functions called in HTML exist in script.js
- [ ] No broken links or missing file references
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets, tokens, or passwords in any file

## Project files
- [ ] `.gitignore` exists at root
- [ ] `README.md` exists at root
- [ ] `netlify.toml` exists if project is deployed to Netlify
- [ ] `package.json` exists if Node.js tooling is used or planned

## Git hygiene
- [ ] `.cursor/mcp.json` is in `.gitignore` (contains tokens)
- [ ] No `node_modules/`, `.env`, or `.netlify/` tracked by git
- [ ] Commit message is clear and present-tense

## Performance
- [ ] No unused CSS blocks
- [ ] No unnecessary external libraries loaded
- [ ] Images use `loading="lazy"` where applicable

## Mobile & accessibility
- [ ] Viewport meta tag present
- [ ] All images have `alt` text
- [ ] Buttons use `<button>`, links use `<a>`
- [ ] Site is usable on mobile (check at 375px width)

## Token-saving rules
- Read only the files needed — not the whole project
- Make targeted edits (StrReplace) instead of rewriting whole files
- Batch independent shell commands with `;` in one call
- Commit multiple fixes in one commit instead of one per fix
- Never restate what was just done — just confirm and move on
